NEW advisor.10.desc:2 "We have found an §SAnomaly§!! From time to time, our §SScience Ships§! will make these discoveries while surveying alien worlds. §SAnomalies§! can be researched by a §SScientist§!, if their skills are up to the task!\n\nDiscovered but unresearched Anomalies are listed under the §SAnomalies§! tab in the §SSituation Log§!. Anomalies must be researched before the planet they were found on can be colonized or otherwise exploited."
OLD advisor.10.desc:0 "We have found an §SAnomaly§!! From time to time, our §SScience Ships§! will discover strange things while surveying worlds. These can be researched by §SScientists§!, but be certain their skills are up to the task!\n\nShould the research effort fail, there is a small chance of losing either the scientist or the science ship... or, if we are especially unlucky, both."
CN  advisor.10.desc:2 "我们发现了§S异常现象§!！我们的§S科研船§!在勘察世界时，偶尔会发现奇怪的事物。§S科学家§!可以研究它们，但要确保他们具备足够的技能才行！\n\n如果研究失败，有小几率会损失科学家或者科研船……或者，在极其不幸的情况下，两者都会损失。"
CHANGE  advisor.10.desc:2 "我们发现了一处§S异常§!！我们的§S科研船§!在勘察外星球时，偶尔会发现这些事物。§S科学家§!可以研究§S异常§!，如果他们的技能足以胜任！\n\n发现但未研究的异常列在§S情报日志§!的§S异常§!标签下。如果要殖民或以其它方式开发行星，必须先研究行星上发现的异常。"
NEW advisor.26.desc:3 "One of our first priorities should be to §SSurvey§! our neighboring star systems. Their resources, and any habitable planets, will remain unknown to us until this has been accomplished. While slow at first, a §SScience Ship§!'s §SSurvey speed§! increases as its assigned §SScientist§! grows more experienced.\n\nTo begin surveying, select our §SScience Ship§! and click on the §SSurvey§! order. Then go to the §SGalaxy Map§! and click on an unsurveyed system that borders our home system. Note that the ship will now move to that system and survey all of its planets in turn."
OLD advisor.26.desc:1 "One of our first priorities should be to survey our neighboring star systems. Their resources, and any habitable planets, will remain unknown to us until this has been accomplished.\n\nTo begin surveying, select our §SScience Ship§! and click on the §SSurvey§! order. Then go to the §SGalaxy Map§! and click on an unsurveyed system that borders our home system. Note that the ship will now move to that system and survey all of its planets in turn."
CN  advisor.26.desc:3 "我们的首要目标是勘察我们相邻星系里的所有天体。勘察完成之后就可发现天体上储存的资源和那些可居住的行星。\n\n想要开始勘察，请选择我们的§S科研船§!并点击§S勘察§!命令。然后进入§S银河系地图§!并点击与我们家园星系相邻的未勘察星系。注意，该飞船将移动到该星系并依次勘察其中的所有行星。"
CHANGE  advisor.26.desc:3 "我们的首要目标是§S勘察§!我们相邻星系里的所有天体。勘察完成之后就可发现天体上储存的资源和那些可居住的行星。最初比较慢，但§S科研船§!的§S勘察速度§!随任命的§S科学家§!经验的丰富而加快。\n\n想要开始勘察，请选择我们的§S科研船§!并点击§S勘察§!命令。然后进入§S银河地图§!并点击与我们家园星系相邻的未勘察星系。注意，该飞船将移动到该星系并依次勘察其中的所有行星。"
NEW tutorial.55.desc:4 "We have uncovered a §SStrategic Resource§!! Many §SStrategic Resources§! require specific technologies to exploit, but can confer powerful bonuses.\n\nDon't forget to build §SStarbases§! where appropriate to secure the resources within our borders. The effects of Strategic Resources do not stack, but controlling more than one source lets us trade the resource to another empire."
OLD tutorial.55.desc:3 "We have uncovered a §SStrategic Resource§!! §SStrategic Resources§! are, surprisingly enough, of strategic value. They give powerful bonuses to anyone possessing them. We should build a §SMining Station§! to procure this precious boon.\n\nDon't forget to build §SStarbases§! where appropriate to secure the resources within our borders. The effects of Strategic Resources do not stack, but controlling more than one source lets us trade the resource to another empire."
CN  tutorial.55.desc:4 "我们找到了一处§S战略资源§!！§S战略资源§!具有很重要的战略意义。通过它们获得强大的奖励。我们应当建造一个§S采矿基地§!以获得这个宝贵恩赐。\n\n不要忘记建造§S太空基地§!保证这些资源位于我们境内。战略资源的作用不会叠加，但是控制多个来源可以将资源用于与其他帝国的交易中。"
CHANGE  tutorial.55.desc:4 "我们找到了一处§S战略资源§!！很多§S战略资源§!需要特定的科技才能开发，但能够得到强大的奖励。\n\n不要忘记建造§S太空基地§!保证这些资源位于我们境内。战略资源的作用不会叠加，但是控制多个来源可以将资源用于与其他帝国的交易中。"
NEW tutorial.560.desc:5 "Using recently-developed technology, an already-extant §SMining Station§! can now mine a §SStrategic Resource§!. These rare resources confer powerful bonuses and make for valuable trade goods. Two metaphorical avians, allegorically struck down by an imaginary projectile.\n\nMore information can be found in the §SSituation Log§! for a time. There are many more §SStrategic Resources§! left to discover in the galaxy, so keep on researching!"
OLD tutorial.560.desc:3 "A new technology has revealed that we already have a §SMining Station§! conveniently placed above a previously unknown §SStrategic Resource§!. These rare resources give powerful bonuses to whoever controls them. Two metaphorical avians, allegorically struck down by an imaginary projectile.\n\nMore information can be found in the §SSituation Log§! for a time. There are many more §SStrategic Resources§! left to discover in the galaxy, so keep on researching!"
